El Baúl del Tiempo es un proyecto con el que queremos crear un espacio y utilizar nuestro tiempo libre para disfrutar de lo que más nos gusta. Somos un equipo de aficionados que queremos compartir experiencias de nuestros hobbies favoritos. Pensamos que la experiencia es mejor compartirla y crear una comunidad de fans para fans es nuestro objetivo.

Tenemos una máxima que dice: “Dédicate a lo que te apasiona y no tendrás que trabajar en tu vida.” De eso se trata esto, de disfrutar compartiendo lo que más nos gusta y construir un proyecto juntos, simplemente porque nos apasiona.

Todo el contenido que se publicará, tanto aquí como en el resto de redes, serán un punto de vista y por lo tanto criticable, no pretenderemos imponer nuestro criterio en ningún momento.

De todo corazón deseamos que lo disfrutes tanto como nosotros.

My name is Ben and I'm the CEO of Wavemaker Stoke

Wavemaker Stoke is about ‘making making work’.

Wavemaker is the delivery and implementation of a three year programme for Comic Relief on behalf of Robbie Williams’ Give it Sum and Nominet Trust about opening an iconic maker space for designer makers, learners and experts in North Staffordshire, the creative county.

Our bigger aim is to create an iconic space where designer makers can inspire makers of tomorrow. Utilising industry leading technology to bring together and support learners, makers and experts. Using innovative learning concepts within a community designed space, we will shape the future for making. Even though the funding is for three years we are already looking at a ten year business plan and further funding including large capital bids.

We plan to address a range of problems, in Stoke on Trent and further afield.
Which include:
• the gap in digital skills with young people, specifically the skills for the future.
• lack of opportunities for young people and others to access digital spaces/opportunities and ones that are of quality.
• lack of opportunity to share skills and knowledge between professionals and budding learners/makers

We want to have a space where learners mix with makers and experts. Ask questions, problem solve, deconstruct and rebuild and to provide opportunities to develop their skills.

If you want to know more then please get in touch.

Hello!

I'm a grad student currently working with the Solheim Additive Manufacturing Lab at the University of Washington in Seattle.
I've got nearly a decade of solid modeling experience, and I love getting to see other people make use of my work.

Mechanical Engineer, Thing-o-Matic Builder, designer and Maker. I mostly design jewellery items and packaging for electronic devices. My designs tend to be highly parametric, or make use of programming to allow for complex shapes, rapid iteration, re-use and customisation. I use a mixture of hand fabrication methods, machining, stock parts, and outside prototyping companies to create final items.
